Rhoplaophthalmus orientalis

can be distinguished from its congeners, which have a combination of following features: 
1
) the antennal sympod with two stout spines and one or two much smaller lateral spines, 
2
) the antennal scale barely reaching the end of the antennular peduncle, and 
3
) the telson possessing a marked “waist” near base.

Distribution. This species has been recorded with certainty from shallow coastal waters of Japan (
Nakazawa 1910
;
Tattersall 1957
;
Ii 1964
), East China Sea (
Liu & Wang 2000
), and Malacca Strait (
Tattersall 1965 ; present study
).
